  "title": "PROJECT MANAGER",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Lead and work closely with project and other teams to monitor and evaluate all projects; ensure that all works in progress are in-line with the proposed work schedules and budget.</li>\n  <li>Liaising with the Main Contractor, Architects, Consultants, relevant authorities and Sub-Contractors to ensure smooth completion of the projects</li>\n  <li>Work with internal departments to prepare, review and submit all detailed programmers, schedule, method statement, technical proposal, risk assessment plans etc.</li>\n  <li>Ensure all construction activities comply with safety regulations and industry standards.</li>\n  <li>Address issues proactively to minimize disruptions, delays and potential.</li>\n  <li>Identify potential risks and develop mitigation strategies to ensure project continuity.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>At least 10 year experience in Alum and Glazing Design project management works.</li>\n  <li>Excellent leadership and team-building skills with the ability to manage multidisciplinary teams.</li>\n  <li>Strong communication and negotiation skills.</li>\n  <li>Proven experience in cost control, procurement, and supplier management.</li>\n  <li>Ability to work under pressure and meet tight deadlines.</li>\n  <li>Bachelor’s degree in civil engineering or related disciplines</li>\n  <li>Singapore Citizen and Permant Residence are preferred. (Foreigners with relevant experience will also be considered)</li>\n</ul>",
